'''塔馬姆·賽義卜·薩拉姆'''（{{lang-ar|تمّام صائب سلام}}；{{bd|1945年|5月13日|}}），是一名[[黎巴嫩|黎巴嫩]]獨立[[遜尼派|遜尼派]]政治人物<ref name=mou3aug>{{cite news|last=Moubayed|first=Sami|title=Nasrallah and the three Lebanons|url=http://www.atimes.com/atimes/Middle_East/HH03Ak01.html|accessdate=27 March 2013|newspaper=Asia Times Online|date=3 August 2006|archive-date=2013-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511041924/http://www.atimes.com/atimes/Middle_East/HH03Ak01.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，自2014年2月14日出任[[黎巴嫩总理|黎巴嫩总理]]<ref name="aljazeera.com">[http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2014/02/lebanese-pm-unveils-national-unity-cabinet-2014215112754343666.html Lebanese PM unveils national unity cabinet] {{Wayback|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2014/02/lebanese-pm-unveils-national-unity-cabinet-2014215112754343666.html |date=20200807133611 }} ''Al Jazeera''. Retrieved 16 February 2014.</ref><ref name="nytimes.com">[http://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/16/world/middleeast/lebanese-leader-forms-cabinet-after-10-months-of-deadlock.html?_r=0 Lebanon Forms a Cabinet After 11 Months of Deadlock] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/16/world/middleeast/lebanese-leader-forms-cabinet-after-10-months-of-deadlock.html?_r=0 |date=20210125081402 }} ''New York Times''. Retrieved 29 June 2014.</ref>，並於同年5月代理[[黎巴嫩总统|黎巴嫩总统]]。

他雖然為獨立政治人物，但與{{le|3月14日聯盟|March 14 Alliance}}親近，和{{le|3月8日聯盟|March 8 Alliance}}也保持良好關係<ref name=reu5apr>{{cite news|title=Hezbollah bloc to back Salam for Lebanon premier|url=http://in.reuters.com/article/2013/04/05/lebanon-government-hezbollah-salam-idINDEE93408U20130405|accessdate=5 April 2013|newspaper=Reuters|date=5 April 2013|archive-date=2014-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222222148/http://in.reuters.com/article/2013/04/05/lebanon-government-hezbollah-salam-idINDEE93408U20130405|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==生平==
薩拉姆生於[[贝鲁特|贝鲁特]]<ref name=wleaks3march>{{cite news|title=Lebanon Biographies of Potential Prime Ministers Following PM Karami's Cabinet Resignation|url=http://www.cablegatesearch.net/cable.php?id=05BEIRUT654|accessdate=27 March 2013|work=Wikileaks|date=3 March 2003|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004212858/http://www.cablegatesearch.net/cable.php?id=05BEIRUT654|archivedate=2013年10月4日}}</ref>，前總理{{le|賽義卜·薩拉姆|Saeb Salam}}的長子<ref name=mou>{{cite journal|last=Moubayed|first=Sami|title=From Father to Son in Beiruti Politics|journal=Mid East Views|date=n.d.|url=http://www.mideastviews.com/print.php?art=430|accessdate=27 March 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130411090945/http://www.mideastviews.com/print.php?art=430|archivedate=2013年4月11日}}</ref><ref name=yeh2feb>{{cite journal|author=Ranwa Yehia|title=Salam bid farewell|journal=Al Ahram Weekly|date=27 January – 2 February 2000|volume=466|url=http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/2000/466/re3.htm|accessdate=27 March 2013|archive-date=2013-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921054426/http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/2000/466/re3.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=dak5apr>{{cite news|author=Hussein Dakroub|title=Salam emerges as Lebanon’s next PM|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Politics/2013/Apr-05/212660-salam-emerges-as-lebanons-next-pm.ashx#axzz2PVqkb3k2|accessdate=5 April 2013|newspaper=The Daily Star|date=5 April 2013|location=Beirut|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112232029/http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Politics/2013/Apr-05/212660-salam-emerges-as-lebanons-next-pm.ashx#axzz2PVqkb3k2|dead-url=no}}</ref>、奧斯曼帝國與{{le|大黎巴嫩|Greater Lebanon}}時期的官員{{le|薩利姆·阿里·薩拉姆|Salim Ali Salam}}的孫子<ref name=aljaz5apr>{{cite news|title=Lebanon's March 14 camp endorses PM candidate|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2013/04/20134511453853799.html|accessdate=5 April 2013|work=Al Jazeera|date=5 April 2013|archive-date=2020-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200613232446/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2013/04/20134511453853799.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=zat5apr>{{cite news|title=How Tammam Salam Became a Consensual Candidate|url=http://moulahazat.com/2013/04/05/how-tammam-salam-became-a-consensual-candidate/|accessdate=5 April 2013|work=Moulahazat|date=5 April 2013|archive-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116062720/https://moulahazat.com/2013/04/05/how-tammam-salam-became-a-consensual-candidate/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

